<p><strong>Skills</strong> Perception +2, Performance +6, Stealth +5</p>

<p><strong>Languages</strong> Common, Elvish, Sylvan</p>

<p><strong>Challenge</strong> 1/2 (100 XP)</p>

<p><strong><em>Magic Resistance.</em></strong> The satyr has advantage on saving throws against spells and other magical effects.</p>

<p><strong>Actions</strong></p>

<p><strong><em>Ram.</em></strong> Melee Weapon Attack: +3 to hit, reach 5 ft., one target. Hit: 6 (2d4 + 1) bludgeoning damage.</p>

<p><strong><em>Shortsword.</em></strong> Melee Weapon Attack: +5 to hit, reach 5 ft., one target. Hit: 6 (1 d6 + 3) piercing damage.</p>

<p><strong><em>Shortbow.</em></strong> Ranged Weapon Attack: +5 to hit, range 80/320 ft., one target. Hit: 6 (1d6 + 3) piercing damage.</p>

<p><strong><em>Variant: Panpipes.</em></strong> Gentle Lullaby. The creature falls asleep and is unconscious for 1 minute. The effect ends if the creature takes damage or if someone takes an action to shake the creature awake.</p>

